# Chronos ‚Äî Cursor Project Rules

## What this app is
Chronos is a classroom civilisation strategy game. A **teacher** creates a game, generates a hex map, and hands out PINs. **Students** log in as civilisations and play on the hex map in real time. A **projector** view shows the live map on a classroom screen.

Three routes:
- `/teacher` ‚Äî game/civ management, map generation, PIN distribution
- `/student` ‚Äî the player-facing game interface (map + sidebar panels)
- `/projector` ‚Äî read-only live display for classroom projection

---

## Tech stack
- **React 19** with the new JSX transform (no `import React` needed, but use `import type { ReactElement } from 'react'` for return-type annotations ‚Äî do NOT use `JSX.Element`, that namespace is not in scope)
- **TypeScript ~6.0** ‚Äî strict mode; prefer `type` imports for interfaces
- **Vite 8** with `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin
- **Tailwind CSS 4** ‚Äî utility-first; config is minimal, just the Vite plugin
- **Supabase** (`@supabase/supabase-js`) ‚Äî Postgres + Realtime + RPC functions; client is `src/lib/supabase.ts`
- **React Router v7** ‚Äî `<BrowserRouter>` wrapping, three routes in `src/App.tsx`
- No Redux, no Zustand ‚Äî state lives in two React Contexts + component-local state

---

## Directory layout
```
src/
  components/       # Reusable UI components
  contexts/         # AuthContext (Google OAuth), StudentContext (civ session)
  lib/              # Pure utilities: hexUtils, mapGen, presetMaps, statsCalc, supabase
  pages/            # Route-level components: TeacherPage, StudentPage, ProjectorPage
  types/            # Shared TypeScript interfaces (resources.ts)
  index.css         # Global styles ‚Äî Tailwind import + parchment theme CSS
  App.tsx           # Router
  main.tsx          # Entry point, Context providers
```

---

## Key types ‚Äî know these before touching game logic

### `HexCell` (`src/lib/hexUtils.ts`)
```ts
interface HexCell {
  q: number          // column (odd-r offset layout)
  r: number          // row
  terrain: TerrainType
  resource: ResourceType | null
  owner: string | null   // civilization id
  explored_by: string[]
}
type TerrainType = 'plains'|'forest'|'hills'|'desert'|'coast'|'river'|'mountain'|'lake'|'jungle'|'steppe'|'tundra'
type ResourceType = 'wheat'|'wood'|'stone'|'iron'|'gold'|'gems'|'fish'
```

### `Civilization` (`src/contexts/StudentContext.tsx`)
```ts
interface Civilization {
  id: string
  game_id: string
  group_name: string
  username: string
  resources: Record<string, unknown>  // JSONB ‚Äî parse with parseCivResources()
  territory: unknown                   // JSONB
  techs: string[]
  policies: string[]
  action_points: number
  color: string   // hex color e.g. '#4f8ef7'
}
```

### `CivResources` (`src/types/resources.ts`)
```ts
interface CivResources {
  // Core stats (derived each turn)
  population: number;  military: number;  wealth: number;  knowledge: number
  // Trade resources (accumulated from terrain)
  food: number;  timber: number;  gold: number;  stone: number
  // Luxury resources (boolean ‚Äî owning the right hex type grants access)
  spices: boolean;  silk: boolean;  marble: boolean;  horses: boolean;  iron: boolean
}
```

### `GameSettings` (`src/types/resources.ts`)
```ts
interface GameSettings {
  resourceMultiplier: number   // scales all terrain production (default 1.0)
  growthRate: number           // population added per food-surplus point per turn
  militaryMaintenance: number  // gold consumed per military point per turn
  knowledgeRate: number        // knowledge gained per tech per turn
}
```

---

## Game logic (`src/lib/statsCalc.ts`)
- `parseCivResources(raw)` ‚Äî converts raw JSONB to `CivResources` with safe defaults. Always use this instead of reading `civ.resources` directly.
- `calculateStatsForTurn(civ, settings, ownedCells?)` ‚Äî full one-turn simulation: terrain production ‚Üí tech bonuses ‚Üí policy multipliers ‚Üí population/military/knowledge derivation ‚Üí luxury detection.

### Terrain ‚Üí resource mapping
| Terrain  | Produces          |
|----------|-------------------|
| plains   | +2 food           |
| steppe   | +1 food           |
| forest   | +2 timber         |
| jungle   | +1 timber, silk luxury |
| hills    | +2 stone          |
| mountain | +1 stone          |
| coast    | +2 wealth         |
| river    | +1 food, +1 wealth|
| desert/lake/tundra | nothing |

### Luxury resource sources
| Luxury  | Granted by                              |
|---------|-----------------------------------------|
| spices  | hex with `resource === 'gems'`          |
| silk    | `terrain === 'jungle'`                  |
| marble  | `resource === 'stone'` on hills/mountain|
| horses  | `terrain === 'steppe'` or `'plains'`    |
| iron    | `resource === 'iron'`                   |

---

## Hex coordinate system
- **Odd-r offset layout**, pointy-top hexagons
- `hexToPixel(q, r)` and `pixelToHex(px, py)` in `src/lib/hexUtils.ts`
- Default map: 30 cols √ó 20 rows, `HEX_SIZE = 36`
- The map is rendered on an HTML5 Canvas (`MapCanvas.tsx`) ‚Äî no DOM hexes, pure 2D drawing

---

## Visual theme ‚Äî the parchment system

### Two palettes
**Parchment (light) ‚Äî login, StatPanel, any foreground cards:**
- Background: `#f4e4c1` ‚Üí `#eed9a2` ‚Üí `#dfc080`
- Borders: `#7a4e1e` (outer), `#c8a96e` (inner accent)
- Text: `#3a2210` (body), `#5c3312` (labels), `#7a4e1e` (secondary)
- Font: `'Cinzel', serif` for headings/labels/values; `'Uncial Antiqua', cursive` for subtitles

**Dark parchment ‚Äî ResourceBar, header accents:**
- Background: `#1e1208` ‚Üí `#150d05`
- Text/icons: `#c8a96e` (icons), `#e8d5a0` (values)
- Borders: `rgba(200, 169, 110, 0.2)`

### Shared CSS classes (defined in `src/index.css`)
```
.scroll-ornament.top / .bottom  ‚Äî brown rod with ornament-line + ornament-symbol
.scroll-card                     ‚Äî full parchment card with double-border box-shadow
.scroll-body / .scroll-title / .scroll-subtitle / .scroll-divider
.parchment-label / .parchment-input / .parchment-btn / .parchment-error
.pin-input-row / .pin-box
.stat-panel / .stat-grid / .stat-cell / .stat-icon-wrap / .stat-label / .stat-value
.resource-bar / .res-trade-group / .res-trade-item / .res-trade-icon / .res-trade-value
.res-lux-group / .res-lux-badge / .res-lux-owned / .res-lux-absent
```

Always extend existing CSS classes rather than duplicating the color values inline. New parchment-themed components should reuse `.scroll-ornament`, `.parchment-btn`, etc. where possible.

---

## Supabase schema (key tables)
```sql
games (id, world_seed, hex_map jsonb, status, current_turn)
  status: 'lobby' | 'active' | 'paused' | 'review' | 'ended'

civilizations (id, game_id, group_name, username, pin_hash,
               resources jsonb, territory jsonb, techs jsonb,
               policies jsonb, action_points int, color text)
```

### RPC functions
- `verify_student_pin(p_raw_pin, p_username)`, `get_student_play_state`(same keys), `submit_turn_queue(p_raw_pin, p_slots, p_username)` ‚Äî PostgREST arg naming (StudentContext)
- `reset_civ_pin(civ_id)` ‚Üí new plaintext PIN
- `create_civ_with_pin(game_id, username, group_name, color)` ‚Üí civ + PIN

---

## State management
- **`AuthContext`** ‚Äî Google OAuth session (`useAuth()`)
- **`StudentContext`** ‚Äî active civ, login/logout, localStorage persistence under key `chronos_student_civ` (`useStudent()`)
- No global store for game/map state ‚Äî data is fetched per-component from Supabase and passed as props

---

## Component conventions
- Named exports for all components (`export function Foo`)
- Props interfaces defined inline above the component
- `useMemo` for any derived data from `civ.resources` (use `parseCivResources` inside the memo)
- Inline SVG icons defined as plain functions at the top of the file ‚Äî `viewBox="0 0 24 24"`, `fill="none"`, `stroke="currentColor"` so they inherit text color
- No icon libraries are installed ‚Äî build SVG icons by hand or use Unicode symbols in Cinzel font

---

## Coding conventions
- Prefer `const` arrow functions for internal helpers, named `function` declarations for exported components
- Group file sections with `// ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ Section name ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ` comment dividers
- TypeScript: use `Partial<Record<...>>` for sparse lookup tables, `Pick<T, ...>` for subset prop types
- Avoid `any` ‚Äî use `unknown` + type guards instead
- CSS: add new classes to `src/index.css` at the bottom, grouped under a `/* === SECTION === */` header
- No `console.log` left in committed code

---

## What's been built so far
- Hex map generation (procedural + 6 historical presets)
- Canvas map renderer with pan/zoom, terrain sprites, fog of war
- Teacher page: game creation, civ management, PIN system
- Student login: parchment scroll card, PIN input
- Student page: map canvas + sidebar with StatPanel and ResourceBar
- `calculateStatsForTurn` utility covering terrain, tech, policy, population, military, knowledge
- Projector view (read-only map display)

